13/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Justice Ministry official Slobodan Homen said on Monday (April 12th) that alleged trafficker Darko Saric's drug gang planned to kill senior officials and those investigating the group. He confirmed that President Boris Tadic, organised crime prosecutor Miljko Radisavljevic and Justice Minister Snezana Malovic have all received threats. Saric is wanted by Serbia for cocaine trafficking. (RTS, Tanjug, Btea - 12/04/10)
